accessibility statement for colorado technical education colorado community college system cccs committed ensuring digital accessibility for people with disabilities are continually improving the user experience for everyone and applying the relevant accessibility standards measures support accessibility colorado community college system cccs takes the following measures ensure accessibility the colorado technical education website marginleft people with disabilities our design process appointed developer and designer lead the accessibility the website used multiple tools and screen readers facilitate accessibility testing conformance https www org wai standards guidelines wcag the web accessibility guidelines wcag defines requirements for designers and developers improve accessibility for people with disabilities defines three levels conformance level level and level aaa the colorado technical education website partially conformant with wcag level partially conformant means that some parts the not fully conform the accessibility standard fontstyle italic additional accessibility considerations although our goal wcag level conformance have also applied some level aaa success criteria such marginleft after session expires does not cause loss flashes more than times per second the user can submit information the submission reversible verified confirmed aria used where appropriate enhance html semantics better identify the purpose html5 regions aria landmarks are used identify regions feedback welcome your feedback the accessibility colorado technical education know you encounter accessibility barriers the colorado technical education website marginleft mail href mailto cte cccs edu cte cccs edu visitor address east lowry boulevard denver try respond feedback within business days assistive technology compatibility colorado technical education designed compatible with the following assistive technologies marginleft nvda windows voiceover mac chrome with chromevox assistive technology browser compatibility colorado technical education fully compatible with marginleft chrome firefox colorado technical education has not had compatibility tested with marginleft safari edge samsung internet opera mobile interfaces limitations and alternatives despite our best efforts ensure accessibility colorado technical education there some limitations below description known limitations and potential solutions contact href mailto cte cccs edu cte cccs edu you observe not listed below known limitations for colorado technical education marginleft multi fields universal contacts grants and reports the multi fields are not keyboard functional have documented the and have the backlog address highlights collections grants and cta wcag level dictates should not the only visual means conveying information mitigate this have included instructions explain the meaning the highlights and only used highlighting indicate peripheral information that not one job improvement plan grants the improvement plan not read properly multiple screen readers work around you can access the same information the public perkins metrics institution report public reporting found here have documented the and have the backlog address after this was built future tables were built using code and which are properly read multiple screen readers screen has been designed viewed with 1080p monitor with available pixel your monitor older and does not meet this resolution you are using laptop with smaller screen some potentially distorted some workarounds available are collapse any side trays well decrease the the browser using the built zoom functionality for your specific browser system multiple labels throughout the there are fields that have multiple labels while the accessibility testing tools indicate that this could confusing those using screen readers both chromevox and voiceover not read multiple labels when translating the the has been documented and the backlog address graph contrast for each report webpage there and graph for the graphs most colors are accessible according wcag contrast standards however some are not the colors were chosen because their contrast with each other making lines easier distinguish one another apologize that this however mitigate this increased the and the the additionally the graphs visual supplement the tables the graphs are difficult read rely using screen reader read the tables assessment approach colorado community college system cccs assessed the accessibility the colorado technical education website the following approaches marginleft formal quality assurance process throughout the design and development process utilizing wave axe lighthouse chromevox nvda and voiceover formal approval this accessibility statement this accessibility statement approved director cte accountability and perkins plan manager the colorado community college system formal complaints contact href mailto cte cccs edu cte cccs edu this statement was created december using the https www org wai planning statements w3c accessibility statement generator
